## How to Start Training

### Step 1 — Install dependencies
```bat
# Option A: One-click (recommended)
install_and_train.bat

# Option B: Manual
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Step 2 — Train the model
```bat
python train_model.py
```

**Expected output flow:**
```
✅  GPU detected: NVIDIA GeForce RTX ...     ← or CPU fallback
📂  Loading dataset: master_crop_dataset.csv
  Dataset shape  : (68290, 14)
  Unique classes : 22
🔍  Running Optuna HPO — 150 trials …
  Best CV accuracy : 99.xxxx%
📊  Running 10-Fold Stratified Cross-Validation …
  CV Accuracy  : 99.xxxx% ± 0.xxxx%
🚀  Training final model ...
💾  All artifacts saved to ./model_artifacts/
🎯  Final Test Accuracy : 99.xxxx%
```

> [!TIP]
> If you want faster training during testing, reduce `OPTUNA_TRIALS = 30` and `CV_FOLDS = 5` at the top of `train_model.py`.

### Step 3 — Evaluate & test
```bat
python evaluate_model.py
```
This will:
- Show full accuracy report on the held-out `test.csv`
- Simulate 5 live ESP32 sensor payloads end-to-end
- Run 3 edge-case stress tests (zero inputs, max inputs, neutral)

