## Expected Accuracy Range

Based on the dataset characteristics (68K rows, well-separated agronomic features, 22 classes):

| Metric | Expected Range |
|---|---|
| Top-1 Accuracy | **98.5 – 99.8 %** |
| Top-3 Accuracy | **99.9 – 100 %** |
| F1 Macro | **98 – 99.7 %** |
| CV Mean | **98.5 – 99.6 %** |

> [!NOTE]
> The 13 engineered features (N_P_ratio, THI, water_availability, pH_stress, etc.) are the key reason for near-perfect accuracy. They encode agronomic domain knowledge that raw N/P/K values alone can't capture.

